1
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:38,200
Hi, Kla. How's it going?
Have you guys finished the lion dance yet?

2
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,400
Uncle Lit fell off the pole.

3
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:44,400
He's with the doctors now.
I don't think it's too serious.

4
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:52,800
Blade.

5
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:02,880
CPR.

6
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,520
Mom, don't worry, okay?

7
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,720
Dad's going to be okay.

8
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,560
- Taew.
- I'm here.

9
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:17,240
Mom, what happened? How's Dad?

10
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,280
Dad's with the doctor right now.

11
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,360
They're treating him.

12
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:22,400
How did Dad fall off the pole?

13
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:25,080
Kla, Uncle, how did it happen?

14
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,440
The pole broke apart.

15
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,560
- The pole broke?
- Yeah.

16
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,880
That's impossible. How could it break?

17
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,760
It already happened.
What do you want me to do?

18
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:51,440
That's one full CPR cycle.

19
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,960
- Charge to 150 joules.
- 150.

20
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:02,440
This is the person

21
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,200
who called the ambulance for Lit.

22
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,440
Here.

23
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,800
You should eat something, Auntie.

24
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,840
Your mom hasn't eaten since noon.

25
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,400
Thank you.

26
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,160
Thank you so much.

27
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,720
Doctor, how is my father?

28
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,160
Is he going to be okay?

29
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:39,600
The patient has three fractured ribs.

30
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:43,200
Some of the bones
have punctured the pleura.

31
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,600
His leg is broken.

32
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,760
As for his head,

33
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,680
he also suffered a severe impact,

34
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,680
causing a brain hemorrhage.

35
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:52,640
You can treat my father, right?

36
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:55,480
We've completed the surgery.

37
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:58,680
However,
the patient's condition is still critical.

38
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,280
We'll have to monitor him day by day.

39
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,600
Doctor, please help my dad.

40
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,720
Please do your best.

41
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,240
Please save him.

42
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:07,840
Don't worry.
I'll do my best to take care of him.

43
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:22,840
Thank you.

44
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:36,400
200,000 BAHT

45
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,520
Two hundred thousand?

46
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:42,360
Will Universal Healthcare cover this?

47
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:45,160
He is covered.

48
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:47,960
But in Dad's case,
it was emergency surgery,

49
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,920
and his neurological medication
isn't on the Essential Medicines List.

50
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:54,480
We also used after-hours services, Mom.

51
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:57,560
And that's not including
Dad's recovery stay here.

52
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,600
So I asked them
to give us a rough estimate.

53
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,080
If he stays another five months,

54
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:04,200
we might need a lot more money.

55
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:09,280
Where are we supposed
to find that kind of money?

56
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:16,800
Mom, no matter what, we have to find it.

57
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,520
We have to save Dad first.

58
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:37,160
<i>Sathu.</i> May Lit stay safe

59
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:39,280
and make a full recovery.

60
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:41,040
Once he's back on his feet,

61
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:45,320
our group, Srikhram Krajangfah,
will take over the Mor Lam stage

62
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:49,120
for an all-night concert until dawn.

63
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,920
<i>Sathu.</i>

64
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:53,400
If Mom performs again,

65
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:56,760
I'll wear a beautiful Mor Lam outfit too
and perform folk rock,

66
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:58,360
showing off my fair thighs

67
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:00,520
while dancing all night long.

68
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,920
<i>Sathu.</i>

69
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,720
Aunt Yao's here.

70
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,640
- How's Uncle Lit doing?
- How is he?

71
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:16,720
He's out of danger now, right?

72
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:20,320
Aunt Yao, you've been up all night.

73
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,880
You should get some rest first.

74
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:23,800
Okay, okay. How about this?

75
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:27,440
If anyone wants to know anything,
come ask me.

76
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,520
I'll explain everything.

77
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,120
So where's Taew?

78
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,600
Taew's staying at the hospital
with her dad.

79
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:47,240
EXAMINATION ROOM

80
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:34,120
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

81
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:46,400
- Dad.
- No, you can't!

82
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:48,640
Please don't.
You must not move an injured person.

83
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,480
Dad.

84
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,280
Hey.

85
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:58,880
Hey.

86
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,480
You…

87
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,200
What are you doing here again?

88
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:11,560
Well, I saw everyone else
had already gone home tonight.

89
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,720
You're here all alone,
so I came because I was worried.

90
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,440
So, are you okay?

91
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,800
I'm fine. Thank you.

92
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:24,040
Hey. Hey.

93
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,320
NO ENTRY
STAFF ONLY

94
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,440
Ma'am, visiting hours are over.

95
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,360
- You can't go in.
- Just a second.

96
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:10,280
<i>Dad, I already saw you</i>
<i>check it last night.</i>

97
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:12,560
Can't be too sure.

98
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:16,080
Even if I've already checked it,
I still have to check it again for safety.

99
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,120
- Alright.
- Mm.

100
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,720
How's your dad doing?

101
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:36,040
He still hasn't regained consciousness.

102
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,960
Why did you rush in just now?

103
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,600
Was it because of your nightmare?

104
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:53,000
I dreamed that my dad fell off the pole.

105
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:55,480
Something doesn't feel right to me.

106
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:02,960
Why is that?

107
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,800
Do you think someone did this?

108
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,000
I don't believe it was an accident.

109
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:20,800
Please excuse me.

110
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,840
Taew, what are you doing?

111
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:58,520
Old man, where's the pole Dad climbed?

112
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:03,160
I saw Don and the others
chop it into pieces

113
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,320
and throw it away yesterday.

114
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,080
I can't believe you!

115
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,520
You evil bamboo shoot!

116
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,000
You jinx!

117
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,920
Nobody keeps broken or damaged things.

118
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,120
It's bad luck.

119
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,080
Where did they throw it away?

120
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,160
I want to check
if anyone tampered with it.

121
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,160
Who would do that?

122
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:27,160
It was just weathered,
exposed to the sun, wind, and rain.

123
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,560
So it cracked.

124
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:30,800
If there had been a crack,
Dad would've noticed it.

125
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,280
He checks them all the time.

126
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,360
If the pole wasn't worn out,

127
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,120
then someone must've tampered with it.

128
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,360
Who would tamper with it?

129
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:45,880
We're the only ones who can go in and out.

130
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:49,360
And I'm the only one
who has the shrine key.

131
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:54,760
Or do you suspect me?

132
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,760
Oh, Taew.

133
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,040
Mom.

134
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,400
How's Dad doing?

135
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,640
Has his fever gone up?

136
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,840
He's not getting any better, Mom.

137
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:18,680
Mom, Dad just had surgery yesterday.

138
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:21,800
People who undergo brain surgery
normally take weeks to recover.

139
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,120
We need to stay strong

140
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,200
so Dad can feel it
and keep fighting with us.

141
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:34,040
Ms. Nongyao.

142
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:38,400
Ms. Nongyao.

143
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:40,680
Taew.

144
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:44,360
I need to talk to you about something.

145
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,920
Mr. Chalit owes me two million baht,

146
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,120
and I need the money now.

147
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,040
That's impossible.

148
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:03,120
If Lit owed you money,
he would've told me.

149
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,600
Of course it's possible.

150
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:07,960
Here's the proof.

151
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:17,680
GENERAL LOAN AGREEMENT

152
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:21,480
CHALIT KAENTHAISONG
BORROWER

153
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:22,600
Taew…

154
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:24,960
It really is Dad's signature.

155
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:28,240
HOUSE REGISTRATION

156
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:33,480
THAI NATIONAL ID CARD
MR. CHALIT KAENTHAISONG

157
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:39,440
ONE MILLION BAHT

158
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:41,320
The contract says one million.

159
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,600
How did it become two?

160
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:46,280
Well, it's the interest, Taew.

161
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:47,680
Interest.

162
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:50,760
That's insane.
Twenty percent interest per year?

163
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:54,280
By law,
isn't it supposed to be 15% per year?

164
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:56,800
With interest that high,
Dad never would've agreed to it.

165
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:59,480
Well, who was lending money
during the COVID pandemic?

166
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:05,440
Mr. Chalit practically
begged me for the loan.

167
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:08,400
He said he didn't have enough money
to take care of his family,

168
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:11,680
his wife, his children,
and the lion dance troupe.

169
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:14,120
Think about it. Back then,

170
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,200
did you even have work?

171
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,120
Did you have any income?

172
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:22,960
Well… In that case,

173
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:25,240
could I postpone the payment for now?

174
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:29,120
Right now, with the medical bills

175
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:31,200
and all the other expenses,

176
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:35,200
we're already struggling
just to make ends meet.

177
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:40,000
Then let's do this, Ms. Nongyao.

178
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:42,760
You should sell the land

179
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:45,760
so you'll have money
to pay for Mr. Chalit's treatment

180
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,880
and repay me as well.

181
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,360
Everything will be settled.

182
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:54,280
My dad isn't well right now.

183
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:55,680
The one in debt is my dad.

184
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:58,040
And the land belongs to him too.

185
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:00,400
We'll have to wait until he recovers.

186
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,680
But the interest increases every day.

187
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,600
Just think about it.

188
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:44,360
The Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe is his life.

189
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:48,640
If he found out

190
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:52,480
there wouldn't be the troupe anymore,

191
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,320
how devastated would he be?

192
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:59,320
Mom, please don't say that.

193
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:02,200
If Dad wakes up and hears that,

194
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:05,160
how upset would he be?

195
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:10,880
- Mom.
- Taew.

196
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:15,200
I'm afraid that

197
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,560
if he wakes up

198
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:22,640
and finds out the troupe is gone…

199
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:23,880
Mom.

200
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,520
Don't worry.

201
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,360
I won't give up.

202
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:32,880
Dad promised Grandpa

203
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:36,200
that the Kimhan Troupe
would still be around.

204
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:41,240
Dad, please wake up and be my strength.

205
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:57,120
Three million?

206
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,720
I don't have that for you.

207
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,880
I heard your dad

208
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,240
borrowed money
from Kamnan Danai too, right?

209
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,760
That's a huge debt.

210
00:17:04,839 --> 00:17:08,000
I don't think
you'd be able to pay me back.

211
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:12,839
Old Man.

212
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,560
I have the title deed as collateral.

213
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:18,319
The appraised value is over three million.

214
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,079
Could you please accept it?

215
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:22,720
No matter how much it's worth,
I won't lend you the money.

216
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:24,960
Go on, take it back and leave.

217
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:28,840
Fine.

218
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:30,760
If you don't want it, fine.

219
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,600
Let's go, Mom.

220
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:35,120
- Taew, but…
- Let's go.

221
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,680
They've just left, Kamnan.

222
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:49,280
Thank you so much.

223
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:52,720
About that favor you asked me for,

224
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,000
I'll take care of it.

225
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:10,720
Lit isn't here right now.

226
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:13,040
What about the lion dance jobs
we already accepted?

227
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:15,760
All the clients have gone quiet.

228
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:19,440
If we're doing them, let me know
so the kids can rearrange their schedules.

229
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:23,720
We have to show up
for the jobs we accepted.

230
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:26,440
Even without a leader,
we still have to do it.

231
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:29,440
The Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe
belongs to all of us.

232
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:32,000
How can we just abandon it?
We have to keep going.

233
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:34,560
Yeah, he's right.

234
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:41,120
Anyway, I really need to apologize

235
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:45,440
for not keeping track of the schedule
and not informing everyone sooner.

236
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:47,280
I understand.

237
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,640
You still have to sell food too.

238
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:53,520
And Lit is seriously injured,
so you need to stay with him.

239
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:56,760
But after these jobs,
we'll probably have to disband.

240
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:59,800
Back then, clients hired us

241
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,840
because of Lit alone.

242
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:14,960
‪Excuse me.

243
00:19:19,320 --> 00:19:20,920
Go, Joi!

244
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:21,840
‪Hey!

245
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,640
Taew!

246
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,280
I'm catching up!

247
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:26,800
Go!

248
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,480
Joi, hurry up!

249
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:35,440
‪Thanks.

250
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:36,520
We made it.

251
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:37,440
‪Thanks.

252
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,160
Thank you.

253
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:43,000
- Here.
- Alright.

254
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:45,760
Hello, Or.

255
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,480
I've got the queue tickets now.

256
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:49,560
I got numbers 2, 3, and 4 in line.

257
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,480
Got it. Thank you very much.

258
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:55,000
Okay, goodbye.

259
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:58,840
- Hello! You're with me again today, Ting.
- Yes.

260
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:02,960
I brought my mom here to sell food.
It's Isan food. Come take a look.

261
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,600
Here it is. Here you go.

262
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:08,200
This is Mama Nongyao chili paste,
authentic Isan food. It smells amazing.

263
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:09,680
It's got the aroma of giant water bug.

264
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:11,880
- What would you like? Take a look.
- Mom.

265
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:14,560
- Let me help you.
- Mom, is it selling well?

266
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:16,760
- It's going pretty well, honey.
- I'll have these.

267
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:18,640
Do you need help with anything?

268
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:22,240
- No, honey. Just collect the money.
- Help Ting collect the money.

269
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:25,320
- Mom.
- Hm?

270
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,880
Here, I made 500 baht.

271
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:28,520
And this

272
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:31,400
is from Sai and Joi, 500 each.

273
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,960
I'm giving it all to you.

274
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:36,240
You kids worked hard for this money.
Keep it for yourselves.

275
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:40,360
It's okay, Mom. I already told them.

276
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,880
They wanted to help Dad.

277
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:46,760
Keep it, Mom.
We'll find a way to earn more.

278
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:52,000
‪Okay.

279
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:55,280
Hey, how's business over here?

280
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,840
- What?
- Hey, everyone! The police are here!

281
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,520
Go down that way!

282
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:01,640
Go, go, scatter!

283
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:03,000
- What's going on?
- The inspectors are coming.

284
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:05,200
- What do we do?
- Let's go, Mom.

285
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,200
DELICIOUS
CURRY AND RICE

286
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:08,160
Come on, hurry.

287
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:09,360
- Pack everything up!
- Go!

288
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:13,320
Let me help.

289
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:15,440
- Taew, come on.
- Go ahead, Mom.

290
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:20,360
Handle the cart.

291
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:21,800
- Move!
- Please make way.

292
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:24,480
- Please make way.
- Hurry!

293
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:25,560
- This way.
- Go, go.

294
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:31,040
Go on ahead!

295
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:34,320
DELICIOUS
CURRY AND RICE

296
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,360
Ow!, Ow!

297
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:39,120
- Mom! Mom.
- Mom!

298
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:42,120
- Mom, are you hurt?
- Mom, are you okay?

299
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,000
- Mom.
- Careful.

300
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,240
Mom.

301
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:47,360
Oh, her hand.

302
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:18,520
Please wait a moment.

303
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:20,880
Ting is waiting to get the cart back.

304
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,560
Alright.

305
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:25,760
Shouldn't you see a doctor, Auntie?

306
00:22:26,360 --> 00:22:28,000
It's okay, really.

307
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:30,800
It's just a small cut.
I already cleaned it, so it's fine.

308
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,080
That way, we won't have to waste money.

309
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:35,120
But your ankle hurts too.

310
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:40,040
It's a little better now.

311
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:41,920
‪Alright.

312
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,720
Thank you so much for helping us.

313
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,240
I'll take care of her myself.

314
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,760
Could I have a moment?

315
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:07,200
I know your father
needs a lot of money right now.

316
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:10,640
So I'd like to propose

317
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:12,560
that you sell the land to us.

318
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:17,040
So it turns out
you're actually working with Ms. Ploy.

319
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:20,320
You got close to us
because of the land, didn't you?

320
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:23,360
Don't waste your time.
I'm not selling, no matter what.

321
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,240
I really want you to think it through.

322
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:32,840
There's no need. I'm not selling it.

323
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:35,640
Why don't we at least hear him out?

324
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:37,080
We need money right now.

325
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:40,360
Mom, I'll figure out the money myself.

326
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,800
Don't worry.

327
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,680
Thank you so much.

328
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:46,960
I admit that I need money.

329
00:23:47,040 --> 00:23:48,760
But I'm not so desperate

330
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:51,000
that I'd sell my benefactor's land.

331
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:52,240
Please leave.

332
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,640
<i>If you want me to stop going camping,</i>

333
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:30,640
you will have to stop climbing poles.

334
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:35,720
How can I stop? It's my job.

335
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:37,720
I'm worried about you.

336
00:24:37,800 --> 00:24:40,240
Dad, you can just do the dance
and let Ting climb.

337
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:41,720
Just teach him.

338
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:45,120
Don't even talk about Ting.
He doesn't like it.

339
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:46,920
He won't do a good job.

340
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,640
But Dad, you're getting older.

341
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:50,680
How many more years
are you going to keep climbing?

342
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:57,480
Well, until I can find someone
to take my place.

343
00:24:57,560 --> 00:24:59,680
I promised Old Man Liang

344
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:02,400
that I'd take good care
of the lion dance troupe

345
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:05,000
to repay his kindness.

346
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:09,840
I absolutely won't
let the troupe end with me.

347
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:42,480
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

348
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:43,960
From now on,

349
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:46,240
I'll lead the troupe in Dad's place.

350
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:47,320
Hey.

351
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:49,720
You're a woman.

352
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:53,440
A woman can't lead a lion dance troupe.

353
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,120
No one's ever done that before.

354
00:25:57,280 --> 00:26:00,040
- Well then, let Ting lead it.
- I can't, Mom.

355
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:02,880
A troupe leader needs plenty of time.

356
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:06,080
I'm still in school. I can't do it.

357
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:08,040
Fine then, don't.

358
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:09,040
I'm not forcing you.

359
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:12,480
How about this instead?

360
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:17,040
Let Kla lead the troupe.

361
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:23,120
Lit once said he wanted Kla
to take over the troupe.

362
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,920
But Kla is a boxer.

363
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:30,400
And he's serious about his training.

364
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:31,760
If talent scouts notice him,

365
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:34,160
he might get to fight on a major stage.

366
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:36,160
Being a troupe leader means

367
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:38,120
giving your all,
both physically and mentally,

368
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:40,280
and staying with the lion dance
for the rest of your life.

369
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,360
Dad.

370
00:26:45,280 --> 00:26:47,000
I don't want to lead the troupe.

371
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:49,360
We should let Taew do it.

372
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,000
Besides,

373
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,200
I have a lot of training to do.

374
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,080
If I try to do too many things,

375
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:58,440
- something's bound to suffer.
- Then I'll do it myself.

376
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:15,840
Well?

377
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:27,000
Or do you think

378
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:31,360
Kla and I aren't part of this family?

379
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:35,240
It's not about blood at all.

380
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:38,000
Dad and Mom
weren't Grandpa's blood relatives either.

381
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:42,120
But you all have jobs,
and I don't want to take up your time.

382
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:45,240
And right now, the troupe doesn't get

383
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:48,080
as much work as before, so we can't
rely on it as our main income anymore.

384
00:27:48,760 --> 00:27:50,680
The fact that you're all here practicing,

385
00:27:50,760 --> 00:27:52,920
I can't thank you enough.

386
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:55,800
To lead the troupe,

387
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:57,800
you have to be a man.

388
00:27:57,880 --> 00:28:00,480
Lion dancing is a man's path.

389
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:02,480
Lit scolded you over this too.

390
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:04,400
Don't you remember?

391
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:06,920
Yes, I remember.

392
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:09,360
But the most important thing right now is

393
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:11,800
that the Kimhan Lion
Dance Troupe survives.

394
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:15,880
And I'm not going to pass
this responsibility on to anyone else.

395
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,720
Hey, Joi. Where's the drum?

396
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:45,520
Uncle Don took it.

397
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:50,000
Then you two go help him
watch the equipment.

398
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:51,480
I'll check the pole again.

399
00:28:52,720 --> 00:28:54,040
Mm. Let's go, Joi.

400
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:36,480
Mr. Natee.

401
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:49,920
Ms. Taew.

402
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,200
You drive a fancy car
and park in the executive lot too.

403
00:29:57,280 --> 00:30:00,160
You must have
a pretty high position here, huh?

404
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:04,480
A high position?

405
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:06,520
I'm just an employee.

406
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:08,880
I only came to pick up my boss's car.

407
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:15,640
You're still using wooden poles?

408
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:18,440
Why not switch to steel poles?

409
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:20,960
I think they'd be safer.

410
00:30:22,360 --> 00:30:25,520
You're right. Thanks for the suggestion.

411
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,000
You're welcome.

412
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:31,040
You're here for Boss Chat's event, right?

413
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:33,040
Yes.

414
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:35,120
Do your best, okay?

415
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:38,800
I'm rooting for you.

416
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:43,680
Yes.

417
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,520
‪KIMHAN

418
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:57,600
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

419
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:06,040
Hello, Boss Chat.

420
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:07,680
Hello.

421
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:13,240
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

422
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:39,560
Dad. Dad.

423
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:41,520
What's going on?

424
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:43,680
What's wrong with the drum?

425
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:46,600
Just follow along, Dad.

426
00:31:52,520 --> 00:31:53,800
What kind of drumming is that?

427
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:55,040
Sounds like someone's beating on a can.

428
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:57,360
The Kimhan Troupe is a total mess.

429
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:59,440
The head goes one way, the tail another.

430
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:00,760
It's like they never practiced.

431
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:04,240
Even a scammer troupe could do better.

432
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:07,160
This looks like a school performance.

433
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:15,520
Joi! Joi!

434
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,640
Joi, change the plan. Bring it down there.

435
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:19,720
Go.

436
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:53,400
Hey!

437
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:07,160
What the hell?

438
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:09,480
What the hell are you doing?

439
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:12,360
Grandpa, I already told you
to hire different performers.

440
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:14,480
Mr. Chalit is still in the hospital.

441
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:16,840
See? Without their leader,

442
00:33:16,920 --> 00:33:17,960
they're falling apart.

443
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:19,960
I think we should head right to the event.

444
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,240
We're not even getting paid.

445
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:42,880
And now the drum's ruined.

446
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:44,800
So frustrating!

447
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:47,520
- Damn it.
- Their shop is huge,

448
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:50,560
but they're so heartless
they won't even pay us.

449
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:51,720
<i>Sathu.</i> I hope they go bankrupt.

450
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:53,160
If not today, then another day.

451
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:55,680
If not Monday, then Tuesday.

452
00:33:55,760 --> 00:33:57,680
Any day from Monday to Friday.

453
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:59,280
- I hope their parents--
- Joi!

454
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:01,120
Don't curse them.

455
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:04,040
It's my fault for
not checking the drum carefully enough.

456
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:06,240
At least you realize that.

457
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:12,800
Come on, everyone makes mistakes.

458
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:15,760
Right, Dad?

459
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:19,199
Huh…

460
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:20,960
But yesterday after rehearsal,

461
00:34:21,040 --> 00:34:23,040
I saw you check the drum already,
didn't I?

462
00:34:26,239 --> 00:34:27,520
Yes.

463
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:29,040
I'm so confused.

464
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:31,400
The wooden frame is still solid.
How could it break?

465
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:36,520
I think Dad falling off the pole
and the drum tearing

466
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:37,920
might not have been accidents.

467
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:39,239
Taew.

468
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:42,320
Lit fell off the pole because it was old.

469
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:43,719
It was just worn out over time.

470
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:46,600
And this drum.
I've had it since I was a young man.

471
00:34:46,679 --> 00:34:48,000
We've never replaced the drumhead once.

472
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:50,280
Of course it's going to wear out
and tear eventually.

473
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:54,719
Or do you suspect us?

474
00:34:58,600 --> 00:34:59,840
Huh?

475
00:35:26,520 --> 00:35:28,160
Hope he doesn't snitch on us.

476
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:31,520
He wouldn't dare. He doesn't want to die.

477
00:35:32,440 --> 00:35:34,120
Otherwise, he would've talked already.

478
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:37,000
But if he opens his mouth,

479
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:40,240
use this video to blackmail him.

480
00:36:49,680 --> 00:36:52,360
<i>I think Dad falling off the pole</i>
<i>and the drum tearing</i>

481
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:53,360
<i>might not have been accidents.</i>

482
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:54,680
Taew.

483
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:57,760
Lit fell off the pole because it was old.

484
00:36:57,840 --> 00:36:59,080
It was just worn out over time.

485
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:00,600
‪Ah!

486
00:37:01,200 --> 00:37:02,320
<i>If the pole isn't worn down,</i>

487
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:04,240
then someone must've tampered with it.

488
00:37:04,320 --> 00:37:05,600
Who would tamper with it?

489
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:08,040
We're the only ones who can go in and out.

490
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:09,440
And I'm the only one

491
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:11,200
who has the shrine key.

492
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,240
Or do you suspect me?

493
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:34,480
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
